Argentina captain, Lionel Messi, has warned his teammates over the threat posed by Brazil forward, Neymar Jr, ahead of the Copa América final on Sunday. Messi and his teammates qualified for the final following a nervy penalty shootout against Colombia. The game ended 1-1 after 120 minutes and Emiliano Martinez produced three saves in the ensuing shoot-out. This weekend’s game represents another opportunity for Messi to finally win a major trophy with his country But standing in there are hosts Brazil and Messi’s former Barcelona teammate Neymar Jr. “Brazil, with Neymar, are going to be very difficult. “We know his potential, what he does individually,” Messi said according to Sport. The final will take place at Maracana at 1am UK time (2am Spanish time) on Sunday morning.